ctors outside the family (marital quality, work roles, cultural influences). The book concludes with a useful review of coping strategies and interventions that have been demonstrated to alleviate parenting stress.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aParent and childxPsychological aspects. 0aParentingxPsychological aspects. 0aParentsxPsychology. 0aStress (Physiology). 0aStress (Psychology). 7aSELF-HELP / Self-Management / Stress Management.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z97831105379940 cprintz978030010393940uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030013393640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300133936423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300133936/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY